title: Calculus 7th edition Stewart c2012 Student Solutions Manual
description:
Student Solutions Manual for Calculus, 7th edition (c2012), by James Stewart.

The SSM comes in two parts: Single-variable and multivariable calculus.
full calculus (ch 1-17) = single variable calculus (ch 01-11) + multivariable calculus (ch 10-17)

FILE INFO (both): paginated, bookmarked and true PDF. Files are foldered.

PS:
- problem set regular version (above) = problem set early transcendentals (ET) version (but distributed differently over the whole textbook).
- regular version: transcendental functions dealt with in a dedicated chapter *after* the derivative and integral concepts have been introduced with regular functions.
- ET version: transcendental functions introduced early and dealt with regular functions as the derivative and integral concepts are being introduced.

===> this SSM can be used, albeit indirectly (different problem numbers), with the Early Transcendentals version textbook of the same edition.
